  "text": "DNA extraction from each ear of rodents and any parasites within was done using the previous studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] were used to amplify the ITS1-5.8S-ITS2 fragment for the second stage of the nested PCR (2). For PCR amplification, DNA of known L. major was used as a positive control and PCR water as a negative control. PCR products were directly sequenced to identify Leishmania species, strains and haplotypes infecting individual rodent, and all haplotypes were identified to species by phylogenetic analysis. To do this, DNA sequences were edited and aligned using Sequencher 4.10 software for PC, and the multiple alignments of new DNA haplotypes and homologous GenBank sequences were exported into MEGA software for phylogenetic analysis.",
